section.def:
Appellant
                (上訴人) means, where 2 or more appeals have been
            consolidated, the appellant directed to be the Appellant by the Appeal Committee;

application
                (申請) does not include an application for leave to
            appeal within the meaning of Part II;

Case
                (案由述要) means the Case required to be filed by
            each party to an appeal under Part VII;

file
                (送交存檔) means to file in the Registry of the
            Court;

party
                (一方) means the Appellant and any
            Respondent;

Record
                (文案) means the papers relating to an appeal
            required to be placed before the Court in accordance with Part VIII;

paragraph.content:
further explanation of or argument with respect to, a matter or contention
                    already included in that party’s Case;
                    or
